review_blob: Plain nasty.  Looks like beer, smells like morning breath, tastes like almost nothing, then a wierd salty/sour taste registers in my mouth. This is one of very few brews I have ever not at least finished. This isnt really beer, but its really a bad malt beverage.

For the price, one of the better beer deals out there. Could use more hops, a little thin, but very drinkable at 12 bucks an 18 pack (bottles!) out the door at my corner store.  Not a great first beer and wont impress your boss, but very satisfactory overall.  Added bonus: you can play poker with the caps!

I grew up sneaking this one out of my grandfathers fridge in Pottsvile, PA.  Solid all around beer.  Decent color, smooth taste, and halfway decent mouth feel.  Very nice head for an inexpensive brew.  Smuggled a case home in my luggage.

Really excited about this one, but was left disappointed.  Interesting nose, kinda funky and weird, reminded me of the smell of a spit bucket.  Not sure I liked it, but at this price I was really trying.  I will say great color!  The flavor was also a bit weird, almost like drinking one of those beer coctails that were popular in the 90s.  Cant say I particularly enjoyed it, but Im glad I tried.
Have had it in both bottle and tap.  One of my favorite IPAs.  Best value among the Dogfish Head line. Great nose, looks nice, feels good in the mouth and I just really like the way it tastes.

Nice alternative to the usual south-of-the border suspects.  Certainly Mexican, in a good way.  Twist cap!  Deeper in color than Corona and Pacifico. Nice bit of skunkyness on the nose. Medium head, drinks easy and very refreshing.  A buck cheaper than Corona and I liked it better.

Fell in love with this stuff on my honeymoon in Tahiti.  (Maybe its the memories, maybe the beer.) 

I thought you couldnt get Hinano in the States, so I was really excited to come across it at AJs in Phoenix.  Very crisp, almost European in flavor, good balance and I liked the hoppiness.  Will go down even better in the summer heat.  Im hooked.
